document_data.Overview:
The Temple of Eilish was beneath the Statue of [[Kalif Maniozimus]]; the temple had actually sunk into the ground after the drying of the Athis, owing to the abandonment of the spells that kept up the city of Pazar.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|36}} People close enough to read the inscription of the statue were at risk of falling into its dome.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|37}}

The dome beneath the statue was the only surviving structure of any note; the {{SIAdj|100|foot|long=yes}} tall structure had a {{SIAdj|70|foot|long=yes|adj=tall}} pile of sand in it. The place was crawling with [[giant spider|giant tarantulas]]. A magically obfuscated inscription warned against disturbing the Vanquished One, referring to Khalitharius. The area leading to Khalitharius's imprisonment chamber was magically password locked; the passwords were held in a scroll room.

Khalitharius's imprisonment chamber was warded by three rows of two statues, each of which projected a magical barrier between the statues. The first barrier was destructive cold, the second barrier was a curtain of powerful electricity, and the third one was an extremely powerful flame shield. Passwords would bypass all of those barriers and were found in the same room. Behind all the barriers was the Star of Aga-Pelar, set above an altar of white [[marble]]; that altar was Khalitharius's prison.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|38-39}}
